Package ristretto.problem.fs.subset

Class FSSubsetSpecies

  • java.lang.Object
    • ec.Species
      • ristretto.problem.fs.subset.FSSubsetSpecies
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ec.Prototype, ec.Setup, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class FSSubsetSpecies
extends ec.Species
    FSSubsetSpecies is a species which can create FSSubsetIndividual. It has been adapted from the original ECJ's VectorSpecies.java (Copyright 2006 by Sean Luke and George Mason University under AFL v. 3.0) to keep the individual's selected features in a Java's TreeSet.

    FSSubsetSpecies also contain a number of parameters guiding how the individual is generated, crossed over and mutated.

    Parameters

    base.n-features
    int >= 1    		 (the total number of features in the feature selection problem)
    base.min-size
    int >= 1, < n-features    		 (the minimum size of the genome)
    base.max-size
    int >= min-size, < n-features    		 (the maximum size of the genome)
    base.min-feature
    int >= 0, < n-features    		 (the minimum feature index)
    base.max-feature
    int >= min-feature, < n-features    		 (the maximum feature index)
    base.mutation-prob
    0.0 <= double <= 1.0     		(probability that a gene will get mutated over default mutation)

    Default Base
    fs-subset.species
